♪ These arms are yours forevermore, my love ♪

00:36:20.811 --> 00:36:22.585
Sorry… I'm late.

00:36:24.422 --> 00:36:25.515
You're here. That's enough.

00:36:36.939 --> 00:36:40.284
(And the team that wins
the Popular Vote is…)

00:36:40.461 --> 00:36:42.642
(Cat-Cheer Café!)

00:36:42.762 --> 00:36:43.762
Yes!

00:36:44.161 --> 00:36:46.326
Guess giving up my airtime
was worth it after all.

00:36:46.910 --> 00:36:49.002
Next, Granny Juu, please.

00:36:50.871 --> 00:36:52.593
Dr. Pom had an urgent matter today.

00:36:52.666 --> 00:36:54.498
Another vet will check her up instead.

00:36:55.960 --> 00:36:59.677
Oh? Where did he go?

00:36:59.856 --> 00:37:01.913
His date just got back from overseas,

00:37:01.930 --> 00:37:03.706
so he had to go to the airport.

00:37:09.382 --> 00:37:11.392
Oh, it's fine then.

00:37:11.816 --> 00:37:15.051
I just remembered…
I forgot to feed the cats.

00:37:16.229 --> 00:37:17.833
I'll come back another day.

00:37:18.950 --> 00:37:19.950
Sure.

00:37:26.014 --> 00:37:29.704
So where's the cat
I need to check on for Dr. Pom?

00:37:30.474 --> 00:37:32.222
They just went back.

00:37:46.416 --> 00:37:48.941
Hey, why did you lock the doors?

00:37:49.224 --> 00:37:50.530
Leo's not back yet.

00:37:51.242 --> 00:37:53.047
I'm locking the doors
to interrogate some cats

00:37:53.476 --> 00:37:55.276
for teaming up to trick me.

00:37:57.445 --> 00:38:00.808
If I'd told you,
would you have let me go on stage?

00:38:01.435 --> 00:38:03.016
You don't like crowds, do you?

00:38:04.231 --> 00:38:05.596
And you didn't even rehearse.

00:38:05.787 --> 00:38:06.787
That's true.

00:38:07.907 --> 00:38:09.763
But I wanted to be on stage
with my boyfriend.

00:38:10.373 --> 00:38:12.001
So I wanted to be childish for one day.

00:38:15.980 --> 00:38:19.595
I'm sorry… for saying
hurtful things the other day.

00:38:24.421 --> 00:38:25.421
Now…

00:38:26.790 --> 00:38:27.830
I understand.

00:38:29.636 --> 00:38:31.730
Our love may look different,

00:38:33.212 --> 00:38:34.227
but it's equal.

00:38:38.573 --> 00:38:40.684
(Ahem! Dinner time, guys.)

00:38:44.139 --> 00:38:45.507
I'll bring the cats to their room.

00:38:49.285 --> 00:38:50.285
Let's go.

00:39:12.684 --> 00:39:13.684
Mom.

00:39:13.982 --> 00:39:16.508
I've only been running this café
for just over a year

00:39:17.909 --> 00:39:19.601
and I already have a trophy to show off.

00:39:20.302 --> 00:39:21.793
Did you ever get one, Mom?

00:39:22.812 --> 00:39:24.027
And it's not just a trophy,

00:39:26.022 --> 00:39:27.115
I got something else too.

00:39:28.271 --> 00:39:30.616
Once you have someone,
I'll get kicked to the curb.

00:39:31.133 --> 00:39:32.418
Don't talk nonsense, Mom.

00:39:32.901 --> 00:39:34.138
Why would I even need someone?

00:39:34.235 --> 00:39:36.277
Being single is the best.

00:39:36.418 --> 00:39:37.428
I don't believe you.

00:39:37.507 --> 00:39:38.543
We'll see about that.

00:39:38.678 --> 00:39:40.194
The only way I'd ever date someone...

00:39:40.428 --> 00:39:42.006
he has to be handsome like a model,

00:39:42.306 --> 00:39:43.625
come from a prestigious family,

00:39:45.103 --> 00:39:46.190
hold a PhD,

00:39:47.132 --> 00:39:48.417
and play for the national team.

00:39:49.763 --> 00:39:51.303
With that list of yours,

00:39:51.453 --> 00:39:53.412
good luck finding that person
in your next life.

00:39:53.932 --> 00:39:54.932
Mom!

00:39:55.695 --> 00:39:58.915
I think the person who can tame you,

00:39:59.182 --> 00:40:00.827
has to be a man who looks fierce,

00:40:01.894 --> 00:40:03.206
smoldering,

00:40:05.052 --> 00:40:07.817
cool, edgy, and dark.

00:40:10.154 --> 00:40:13.101
And he has to pick
the ginger out for you, just like I do.

00:40:14.693 --> 00:40:16.438
You said that like
you could see the future.

00:40:17.800 --> 00:40:19.668
JE MEOW

00:40:19.938 --> 00:40:21.320
What are you talking to her about?

00:40:22.268 --> 00:40:24.531
I'm just showing off the trophy to her.

00:40:26.788 --> 00:40:28.105
Let me say something to her too.

00:40:29.516 --> 00:40:30.516
Je Meow,

00:40:31.831 --> 00:40:33.505
you once told me…

00:40:34.150 --> 00:40:35.614
you'd give me the café and your son.

00:40:36.012 --> 00:40:37.331
I first got the café

00:40:39.951 --> 00:40:43.318
and now I have them both, Mom.

00:40:44.891 --> 00:40:45.891
"Mom"?

00:40:46.862 --> 00:40:48.281
Since when did you become her son?

00:40:51.591 --> 00:40:53.117
I asked them to sell this to me.

00:40:55.000 --> 00:40:59.578
I'd like to put this ring on you

00:41:03.229 --> 00:41:04.229
right here.

00:41:14.746 --> 00:41:15.810
And I hope…

00:41:17.416 --> 00:41:18.663
it stays there for a long time.

00:41:36.451 --> 00:41:37.451
Look!

00:41:38.347 --> 00:41:40.434
Did you ever get
something like this, Mom?

00:41:47.140 --> 00:41:51.507
Now that Je Meow,
Leo, Krapor know about us,

00:41:52.435 --> 00:41:53.873
who's left?

00:41:56.658 --> 00:41:57.658
Dr. Pom.

00:41:58.280 --> 00:41:59.335
I'll tell him myself.

00:42:00.379 --> 00:42:01.736
That's not who I meant.

00:42:02.339 --> 00:42:04.152
I meant my parents.

00:42:05.610 --> 00:42:07.818
Do you… want to meet them?

00:42:18.957 --> 00:42:20.296
Whose phone is this?

00:42:20.611 --> 00:42:23.012
Sorry. I left my phone here.

00:42:24.587 --> 00:42:25.606
Is this the one?

00:42:34.931 --> 00:42:35.741
Yes.

00:42:36.974 --> 00:42:38.742
That's exactly what I've been looking for.

00:42:41.800 --> 00:42:42.850
You mean the phone?

00:42:43.638 --> 00:42:44.648
The person holding it.

00:42:45.491 --> 00:42:48.415
And yes, that phone is mine.

00:42:54.374 --> 00:42:56.094
If I change my mind
and get my cat checked,

00:42:56.896 --> 00:42:57.916
is it too late?

00:42:58.767 --> 00:42:59.656
Not at all.

00:43:00.217 --> 00:43:02.022
I'm Dr. Pug,
Dr. Pom's brother.

00:43:02.790 --> 00:43:04.417
How's she doing?

00:43:06.005 --> 00:43:07.005
Right now?

00:43:07.668 --> 00:43:08.934
Their heart is beating very fast.

00:43:11.220 --> 00:43:12.234
You mean the cat?

00:43:12.268 --> 00:43:13.268
No, me.

00:43:14.383 --> 00:43:17.461
Oh, my name is Leo.

00:43:17.935 --> 00:43:19.002
And though you didn't ask,

00:43:19.292 --> 00:43:20.423
I'm single.

00:43:26.878 --> 00:43:27.681
Noted.

00:43:31.545 --> 00:43:32.827
(Next Episode)
I had something to deal with today.

00:43:32.866 --> 00:43:34.050
I…bring you to meet them tomorrow.

00:43:34.128 --> 00:43:34.761
Tomorrow?

00:43:35.053 --> 00:43:36.000
Isn't that too soon?

00:43:36.061 --> 00:43:38.023
Oh! You're the one from the cat café.

00:43:38.350 --> 00:43:40.514
Actually… Lynx and I are…

00:43:40.736 --> 00:43:42.416
Tiger wanted to open a coffeeshop,

00:43:42.452 --> 00:43:43.832
so he asked me to be his business partner.

00:43:44.159 --> 00:43:45.622
Why did you lie to my mom like that?

00:43:45.837 --> 00:43:46.951
Your mom wouldn't be happy…

00:43:47.017 --> 00:43:48.506
because she wants a grandchild.

00:43:51.589 --> 00:43:52.922
Can I sleep here tonight?